        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare genetic immune disease characterized by infantile or childhood onset of combined immunodeficiency with recurrent viral bacterial and fungal infections severe autoimmunity mainly manifesting as antibody-mediated destruction of red blood cells platelets and neutrophils and mild to moderate developmental delay. Laboratory findings include decreased circulating T- B- and natural killer cells and hypergammaglobulinemia."
        },
